findings.remediation:
Add a validation block to `var.allowed_range` that rejects `0.0.0.0/0`/`::/0`, e.g.:

  validation {
    condition     = alltrue([for cidr in var.allowed_range : !contains(["0.0.0.0/0", "::/0"], cidr)])
    error_message = "allowed_range must not include 0.0.0.0/0 or ::/0."
  }

Consider also cross-validating that `authorization == "NONE"` is only permitted when `allowed_range` is non-trivially scoped.
